524c			; var handler 
524c			 
524c			 
524c			.VARS: 
524c				CWHEAD .V0 99 "VAR" 3 WORD_FLAG_CODE 
524c 77				db WORD_SYS_CORE+99             
524d bb 52			dw .V0            
524f 04				db 3 + 1 
5250 .. 00			db "VAR",0              
5254				endm 
# End of macro CWHEAD
5254			; | VAR ( u1 -- )  Get the address of the (word) variable referenced on TOS  | DONE 
5254			; | 
5254			; | | The variable name should consist of a single letter (a-z). e.g. "a" 
5254			; | |  
5254			; | | e.g. 
5254			; | |         #30 a var ! 
5254			; | |         a var @ . 
5254			; | |   
5254			; | |     Displays the number 30 
5254			; | | 
5254			; | | Each variable pointer is a word so can use for any words that use that:  
5254			; | |  
5254			; | | e.g. 
5254			; | |  
5254			; | |         #30 a var 2! 
5254			; | |         a var 2@ . 
5254			; | |   
5254			; | |     Displays the number 30 
5254			; | |  
